snippet: Factory activity and retail sales picked up a notch in April, but analysts said expansion remains weak as the Chinese economy undergoes a long-term transition.
abstract: China reports that industrial output rose 9.3 percent in April 2013 from year ago, compared with 8.9 percent rise in March; retail sales rose 12.8 percent in April, compared with 12.6 percent in March; analysts say expansion remains weak as economy undergoes long-term transition.
lead_paragraph: Factory activity and retail sales picked up a notch in April, but analysts said expansion remains weak as the Chinese economy undergoes a long-term transition.

headline.main: April Growth in China Fails to Impress
headline.print_headline: April Growth in China Fails to Impress
